text: Mohamed Said Pashahttps://www.geni.com/people/Said-Pasha- Zulficar/6000000017971439728 () (19 January 1863 - 1928), was Prime Minister of Egypt from 1910 to 1914, and again in 1919. He was born in Alexandria to a family of Turkish origin. He was the father of the artist Mahmoud Sa'id and grandfather of Queen Farida of Egypt. ==References== Category:1863 births Category:1928 deaths Category:Prime Ministers of Egypt Category:Egyptian people of Turkish descent Category:Egyptian pashas Category:Honorary Knights Grand Cross of the Order of St Michael and St George
